---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Poesis">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">THINK · BUILD · RUN</p>
      <h1>Standardizing the THINK layer of IT.</h1>
      <p class="lead">OpenTelemetry standardized how systems are <em>observed</em>. Poesis standardizes how they are <em>defined and governed</em> — then builds and operates the reference implementation, and delivers the transformation around it.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Talk to us</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/standard">Explore the standard</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/products">See the stack</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-note">By the creators of the <a href="/standard">Generative System Model (GSM)</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">The gap</p>
        <h2>Every workload carries obligations no one can port.</h2>
        <p class="lead">Security posture, SLOs, supply-chain provenance, data-protection rules, delivery guardrails, cost ceilings — today they live in tool-specific config and prose, trapped in proprietary silos. The RUN layer got a neutral standard. The THINK layer didn't.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">The closed loop</p>
      <h2>Definitions that generate, run, and correct themselves.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Poesis closes THINK → BUILD → RUN as one governed loop.</p>
      <div class="loop">
        <div class="stage"><div class="k">THINK</div><h3>GSM defines</h3><p>An open model expresses each obligation as a governed definition with a lifecycle.</p></div>
        <div class="stage"><div class="k">BUILD</div><h3>The framework generates</h3><p>The SAFe Agentic Framework turns governed definitions into runnable code.</p></div>
        <div class="stage"><div class="k">RUN</div><h3>The stack runs &amp; reconciles</h3><p>SIE runs it; telemetry observes; governance reconciles definition vs. reality — and round again.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">What Poesis does</p>
      <h2>An open standard, an owned stack, and the transformation around it.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card"><span class="tag">Open</span><h3>The standard</h3><p>GSM — the vendor-neutral model for defining &amp; governing systems. Free, open, the top of every funnel.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><span class="tag tag--muted">Product</span><h3>The stack</h3><p>SIE (the GSM engine &amp; reference implementation) and ITIP (the first domain application) — open-core, SaaS, or on-prem.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><span class="tag tag--muted">Services</span><h3>The transformation</h3><p>AI-generative / agentic transformation of your organization, IT first — with certification for partners and practitioners.</p></div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem"><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">How we engage →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--ink">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why Poesis</p>
      <h2>The reference actor for systemic, AI-native governance.</h2>
      <p class="lead">We wrote the model, we build the canonical implementation, and we run the transformation. The standard maximizes the audience; the product, cloud, services, brand, and certification are where value is delivered.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Start a conversation</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/insights" style="background:transparent;color:#fff;border-color:#334155">Read the thinking</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
